Now, if you've worked with

00:01:16.896 --> 00:01:18.456 A:middle
UITableView or CollectionViews,

00:01:18.456 --> 00:01:19.346 A:middle
you've seen this before.

00:01:19.966 --> 00:01:21.886 A:middle
Here, we're providing three of

00:01:21.886 --> 00:01:24.006 A:middle
the required two methods in this

00:01:24.006 --> 00:01:24.496 A:middle
protocol.

00:01:24.496 --> 00:01:26.676 A:middle
And it's pretty straightforward,

00:01:26.676 --> 00:01:26.836 A:middle
right?

00:01:26.836 --> 00:01:28.466 A:middle
We have asked about the number

00:01:28.466 --> 00:01:29.576 A:middle
of sections and the number of

00:01:29.576 --> 00:01:30.886 A:middle
items in each of those sections.

00:01:31.096 --> 00:01:32.676 A:middle
And as content renders, we're

00:01:32.676 --> 00:01:33.796 A:middle
going to ask for cells.

00:01:34.406 --> 00:01:34.976 A:middle
Pretty straightforward.

00:01:37.056 --> 00:01:38.136 A:middle
And this has served us really

00:01:38.136 --> 00:01:39.566 A:middle
well for about ten years now,

00:01:39.796 --> 00:01:39.936 A:middle
right?

00:01:40.146 --> 00:01:41.686 A:middle
And it's got a couple things

00:01:41.686 --> 00:01:42.186 A:middle
going for it.

00:01:42.186 --> 00:01:42.946 A:middle
It's super simple.

00:01:43.356 --> 00:01:44.266 A:middle
You can reason about it right

00:01:44.266 --> 00:01:44.486 A:middle
away.

00:01:44.486 --> 00:01:46.296 A:middle
If you want to provide just two

00:01:46.296 --> 00:01:48.446 A:middle
methods, the number of items in

00:01:48.446 --> 00:01:49.126 A:middle
a section, if you have a

00:01:49.176 --> 00:01:50.426 A:middle
one-dimensional data source,

00:01:50.426 --> 00:01:51.606 A:middle
that's pretty straightforward.

00:01:52.576 --> 00:01:53.626 A:middle
And you can iterate on it pretty

00:01:53.626 --> 00:01:53.966 A:middle
quickly.

00:01:54.566 --> 00:01:56.566 A:middle
But it's also very flexible,

00:01:56.636 --> 00:01:56.886 A:middle
right?

00:01:56.936 --> 00:01:58.516 A:middle
Because you don't really have to

00:01:58.596 --> 00:02:00.586 A:middle
use any particular kind of data

00:01:58.596 --> 00:02:00.586 A:middle
use any particular kind of data

00:02:00.586 --> 00:02:02.396 A:middle
structure to back your data

00:02:02.396 --> 00:02:02.896 A:middle
source.

00:02:04.116 --> 00:02:05.276 A:middle
It could be as simple as a

00:02:05.346 --> 00:02:06.386 A:middle
one-dimensional array.

00:02:07.426 --> 00:02:08.826 A:middle
And if you had a multi-itemed,

00:02:08.826 --> 00:02:10.906 A:middle
multi-sectioned data source, it

00:02:10.906 --> 00:02:11.796 A:middle
could be two-dimensional, right?

00:02:11.796 --> 00:02:12.256 A:middle
Very simple, very

00:02:12.256 --> 00:02:12.946 A:middle
straightforward.

00:02:15.606 --> 00:02:17.926 A:middle
Well, apps are often a little

00:02:17.926 --> 00:02:19.146 A:middle
more complicated than a, you

00:02:19.146 --> 00:02:19.936 A:middle
know, a one-dimensional or

00:02:19.936 --> 00:02:20.706 A:middle
two-dimensional array.

00:02:22.456 --> 00:02:23.446 A:middle
And apps get more and more

00:02:23.446 --> 00:02:24.216 A:middle
complex every year.

00:02:24.216 --> 00:02:25.166 A:middle
They do more things.

00:02:25.166 --> 00:02:26.886 A:middle
Our users demand more features.

00:02:26.886 --> 00:02:29.576 A:middle
And oftentimes, these data

00:02:29.576 --> 00:02:31.316 A:middle
sources are backed by complex

00:02:31.316 --> 00:02:32.746 A:middle
controllers inside of our app.

00:02:33.686 --> 00:02:35.326 A:middle
And these controllers can do a

00:02:35.326 --> 00:02:35.946 A:middle
variety of things.

00:02:35.946 --> 00:02:36.876 A:middle
They can interact with Core

00:02:36.876 --> 00:02:38.676 A:middle
Data, and they could talk to web

00:02:38.676 --> 00:02:39.186 A:middle
service.

00:02:39.186 --> 00:02:40.546 A:middle
They just do a number of

00:02:40.546 --> 00:02:41.426 A:middle
different things.

00:02:41.626 --> 00:02:43.486 A:middle
And I want to visualize this

00:02:43.486 --> 00:02:43.916 A:middle
real quick.

00:02:45.296 --> 00:02:46.906 A:middle
And let's show a conversation

00:02:46.906 --> 00:02:49.166 A:middle
between your UI layer and this

00:02:49.166 --> 00:02:50.166 A:middle
controller layer that's doing

00:02:50.166 --> 00:02:51.576 A:middle
all this heavy lifting to get

00:02:51.576 --> 00:02:52.516 A:middle
your data.

00:02:52.516 --> 00:02:52.786 A:middle
All right?

00:02:53.686 --> 00:02:54.906 A:middle
And the conversation starts out

00:02:54.906 --> 00:02:55.576 A:middle
very civil.

00:02:56.106 --> 00:02:56.846 A:middle
It's like, "Hey, give me a

00:02:56.846 --> 00:02:57.946 A:middle
number of items in a section, or

00:02:57.946 --> 00:02:59.456 A:middle
give me a cell as we render

00:02:59.456 --> 00:03:00.046 A:middle
content."

00:02:59.456 --> 00:03:00.046 A:middle
content."

00:03:00.486 --> 00:03:01.456 A:middle
Very straightforward.

00:03:01.526 --> 00:03:02.956 A:middle
And so far, smooth sailing.

00:03:06.056 --> 00:03:07.276 A:middle
But things get more complicated

00:03:07.276 --> 00:03:08.016 A:middle
over time, right?

00:03:08.016 --> 00:03:09.076 A:middle
You get -- like let's say this

00:03:09.076 --> 00:03:10.516 A:middle
controller has a web service

00:03:10.516 --> 00:03:11.896 A:middle
request that it gets a response

00:03:11.896 --> 00:03:12.366 A:middle
from, right?

00:03:12.366 --> 00:03:14.196 A:middle
It's like, oh, I've got data for

00:03:14.196 --> 00:03:15.776 A:middle
your tweets or whatever, right?

00:03:16.396 --> 00:03:18.096 A:middle
Well, now this controller layer,

00:03:18.196 --> 00:03:19.716 A:middle
which is complex unto itself,

00:03:20.376 --> 00:03:21.926 A:middle
lets the world know, "Hey, I

00:03:21.926 --> 00:03:22.416 A:middle
changed.

00:03:22.416 --> 00:03:23.226 A:middle
Something changed."

00:03:23.846 --> 00:03:25.546 A:middle
All right, so here's where

00:03:25.546 --> 00:03:27.766 A:middle
things get a bit more complex,

00:03:27.796 --> 00:03:27.996 A:middle
right?

00:03:27.996 --> 00:03:31.066 A:middle
So now, it's up to the UI layer

00:03:31.066 --> 00:03:33.486 A:middle
to decide, "Hey, things changed.

00:03:33.486 --> 00:03:34.856 A:middle
Now, I need to -- can change

00:03:34.856 --> 00:03:37.096 A:middle
this into updates for our UI

00:03:37.486 --> 00:03:37.816 A:middle
layer.

00:03:38.486 --> 00:03:40.086 A:middle
And this involves all the

00:03:40.086 --> 00:03:41.426 A:middle
mutations that have to occur

00:03:41.426 --> 00:03:42.256 A:middle
against TableView and

00:03:42.256 --> 00:03:42.756 A:middle
CollectionView.

00:03:42.756 --> 00:03:44.246 A:middle
It can be a bit complex.

00:03:44.246 --> 00:03:46.076 A:middle
And we covered this complexity

00:03:46.076 --> 00:03:48.236 A:middle
last year in our talk Of Tour of

00:03:48.236 --> 00:03:49.086 A:middle
UICollectionView.

00:03:49.946 --> 00:03:51.436 A:middle
And how to construct those batch

00:03:51.436 --> 00:03:53.726 A:middle
updates properly, and mutate

00:03:53.726 --> 00:03:54.636 A:middle
your backing store, all those

00:03:54.636 --> 00:03:54.976 A:middle
kinds of things.

00:03:57.586 --> 00:03:58.596 A:middle
But sometimes, no matter how

00:03:58.596 --> 00:03:59.276 A:middle
hard you try--

00:04:00.516 --> 00:04:02.626 A:middle
[ Laughter ]

00:04:03.126 --> 00:04:04.226 A:middle
You know, things go wrong.

00:04:04.606 --> 00:04:05.586 A:middle
It's an imperfect world.

00:04:07.186 --> 00:04:08.746 A:middle
And judging by the laughter,

00:04:08.886 --> 00:04:10.006 A:middle
you've probably hit this before,

00:04:10.006 --> 00:04:10.246 A:middle
right?

00:04:11.196 --> 00:04:12.336 A:middle
It's not an uncommon thing.

00:04:12.336 --> 00:04:13.756 A:middle
And it's really frustrating,

00:04:13.756 --> 00:04:13.936 A:middle
right?

00:04:13.936 --> 00:04:14.726 A:middle
You hit this, and you're like,

00:04:14.726 --> 00:04:14.996 A:middle
"All right.

00:04:14.996 --> 00:04:15.656 A:middle
What did I do wrong?"

00:04:16.356 --> 00:04:18.875 A:middle
It's me. And as you dig through

00:04:18.875 --> 00:04:20.616 A:middle
your code, okay, fine.

00:04:20.616 --> 00:04:21.716 A:middle
You Google on Stack Overflow,

00:04:21.716 --> 00:04:22.886 A:middle
see what's going on.

00:04:23.206 --> 00:04:25.146 A:middle
And eventually, you might get

00:04:25.146 --> 00:04:26.006 A:middle
frustrated and just call

00:04:26.006 --> 00:04:26.516 A:middle
reloadData.

00:04:26.516 --> 00:04:27.806 A:middle
And we talked about this last

00:04:27.806 --> 00:04:29.506 A:middle
year, and that's fine.

00:04:29.706 --> 00:04:30.266 A:middle
That's correct.

00:04:30.386 --> 00:04:31.616 A:middle
Your app looks okay.

00:04:32.676 --> 00:04:33.736 A:middle
But when you call reloadData,

00:04:33.736 --> 00:04:35.186 A:middle
you get this non-animated

00:04:35.186 --> 00:04:35.616 A:middle
effect.

00:04:36.306 --> 00:04:37.656 A:middle
And it detracts from the user

00:04:37.656 --> 00:04:38.446 A:middle
experience.

00:04:39.836 --> 00:04:41.356 A:middle
So that's not great.

00:04:44.046 --> 00:04:44.506 A:middle
Okay, I want to get

00:04:44.506 --> 00:04:45.816 A:middle
philosophical just for one

00:04:45.816 --> 00:04:46.156 A:middle
slide.

00:04:46.156 --> 00:04:46.896 A:middle
I promise.

00:04:48.136 --> 00:04:48.716 A:middle
What's the problem?

00:04:49.636 --> 00:04:51.786 A:middle
Well, the problem here is

00:04:51.786 --> 00:04:52.456 A:middle
where's our truth?

00:04:53.786 --> 00:04:55.386 A:middle
You know? I mean, who got his?

00:04:55.386 --> 00:04:56.696 A:middle
And who has all the answers?

00:04:57.806 --> 00:04:59.256 A:middle
And the big issue here is that

00:04:59.256 --> 00:05:01.016 A:middle
our data controller -- or it's

00:04:59.256 --> 00:05:01.016 A:middle
our data controller -- or it's

00:05:01.016 --> 00:05:02.186 A:middle
acting as a data source -- has

00:05:02.186 --> 00:05:03.356 A:middle
its own version of the truth,

00:05:03.356 --> 00:05:04.466 A:middle
which changes over time.

00:05:04.946 --> 00:05:06.736 A:middle
And the UI has a version of the

00:05:06.736 --> 00:05:07.136 A:middle
truth.

00:05:08.336 --> 00:05:09.866 A:middle
And the UILayerCode is

00:05:09.866 --> 00:05:11.256 A:middle
responsible for mitigating that,

00:05:11.256 --> 00:05:12.446 A:middle
making sure that it's always in

00:05:12.446 --> 00:05:12.796 A:middle
sync.

00:05:13.526 --> 00:05:15.476 A:middle
As we saw, it's sometimes hard.

00:05:16.816 --> 00:05:18.576 A:middle
So our current approach is error

00:05:18.576 --> 00:05:19.036 A:middle
prone.

00:05:19.726 --> 00:05:20.626 A:middle
And primarily because there's

00:05:20.626 --> 00:05:22.856 A:middle
just no notion of a centralized

00:05:22.856 --> 00:05:22.976 A:middle
truth.

00:05:26.626 --> 00:05:27.196 A:middle
All right, so that's the

00:05:27.196 --> 00:05:27.766 A:middle
state-of-the-art.

00:05:27.766 --> 00:05:28.476 A:middle
That's where we are today.

00:05:28.476 --> 00:05:29.206 A:middle
But where are we going?

00:05:30.546 --> 00:05:31.716 A:middle
Well, I'm happy to announce that

00:05:31.716 --> 00:05:33.726 A:middle
for iOS, TVoS, and MacOS this

00:05:33.726 --> 00:05:35.116 A:middle
year, we're bringing a brand new

00:05:35.636 --> 00:05:36.326 A:middle
approach.

00:05:37.106 --> 00:05:38.046 A:middle
And we're calling this

00:05:38.496 --> 00:05:39.556 A:middle
DiffableDataSource.

00:05:40.516 --> 00:05:44.546 A:middle
[ Cheering and Applause ]

00:05:45.046 --> 00:05:45.576 A:middle
All right, so let's dig in.

00:05:45.576 --> 00:05:45.976 A:middle
What is this thing?

00:05:49.076 --> 00:05:50.126 A:middle
No performBatchUpdates.

00:05:50.126 --> 00:05:50.576 A:middle
Let's go on.

00:05:51.056 --> 00:05:52.356 A:middle
And along with it, all the

00:05:52.356 --> 00:05:53.976 A:middle
crashes, hassles, complexity,

00:05:53.976 --> 00:05:54.776 A:middle
all of the stuff that you don't

00:05:54.776 --> 00:05:56.166 A:middle
want to deal with, has been

00:05:56.166 --> 00:05:56.726 A:middle
jettisoned.

00:05:57.806 --> 00:05:59.086 A:middle
Instead, we have a single method

00:05:59.086 --> 00:05:59.986 A:middle
we call Apply.

00:06:00.546 --> 00:06:01.196 A:middle
What is Apply?

00:06:01.806 --> 00:06:03.176 A:middle
Apply is simple, automatic,

00:06:03.176 --> 00:06:04.496 A:middle
hassle-free diffing.

00:06:07.386 --> 00:06:09.136 A:middle
So we do this with a brand new

00:06:09.136 --> 00:06:10.766 A:middle
construct we call a Snapshot.

00:06:10.826 --> 00:06:12.156 A:middle
And it's a very simple idea.

00:06:12.296 --> 00:06:13.846 A:middle
It's effectively the truth of

00:06:13.846 --> 00:06:14.826 A:middle
the current UI state.

00:06:15.536 --> 00:06:18.306 A:middle
And instead of IndexPaths, it's

00:06:18.306 --> 00:06:20.076 A:middle
an association or a collection

00:06:20.346 --> 00:06:21.816 A:middle
of section identifiers that are

00:06:21.816 --> 00:06:24.066 A:middle
all unique and item identifiers.

00:06:25.336 --> 00:06:26.766 A:middle
And you update these not with

00:06:26.766 --> 00:06:28.736 A:middle
IndexPaths, with identifiers.

00:06:29.486 --> 00:06:30.226 A:middle
All right, let's look at

00:06:30.226 --> 00:06:32.086 A:middle
something visual to see what's

00:06:32.086 --> 00:06:32.666 A:middle
going on here.

00:06:34.156 --> 00:06:35.276 A:middle
Okay, I'm really creative guy.

00:06:35.276 --> 00:06:37.146 A:middle
So we've got these FOO, BAR, and

00:06:37.226 --> 00:06:38.256 A:middle
BIF onscreen, right.

00:06:38.256 --> 00:06:38.936 A:middle
And that's what we're

00:06:38.936 --> 00:06:39.486 A:middle
interacting with.

00:06:39.486 --> 00:06:41.516 A:middle
These are identifiers in our

00:06:41.516 --> 00:06:41.736 A:middle
app.

00:06:43.146 --> 00:06:44.146 A:middle
And let's say that our

00:06:44.146 --> 00:06:45.156 A:middle
controller changed.

00:06:45.156 --> 00:06:46.546 A:middle
And now we've got this brand new

00:06:46.606 --> 00:06:48.316 A:middle
Snapshot that we want to apply.

00:06:49.116 --> 00:06:49.916 A:middle
But this is our current

00:06:49.916 --> 00:06:50.316 A:middle
Snapshot.

00:06:50.316 --> 00:06:52.676 A:middle
How do we get from our new truth

00:06:53.686 --> 00:06:54.676 A:middle
to the current Snapshot?

00:06:56.686 --> 00:06:57.916 A:middle
Well, we can see here we've

00:06:57.916 --> 00:06:59.486 A:middle
configured a brand new Snapshot

00:06:59.486 --> 00:07:01.496 A:middle
with BAR, FOO, and BAZ.

00:06:59.486 --> 00:07:01.496 A:middle
with BAR, FOO, and BAZ.

00:07:01.496 --> 00:07:02.656 A:middle
And we have some items that are

00:07:02.656 --> 00:07:03.656 A:middle
coming along for the ride that

00:07:03.656 --> 00:07:05.036 A:middle
have just changed order, and

00:07:05.036 --> 00:07:06.796 A:middle
then a new item coming in.

00:07:07.516 --> 00:07:10.136 A:middle
So conceptually an Apply knows

00:07:10.136 --> 00:07:11.796 A:middle
about the current state and

00:07:11.796 --> 00:07:12.996 A:middle
knows about the new state, which

00:07:12.996 --> 00:07:14.566 A:middle
are going to apply to the UI

00:07:14.566 --> 00:07:14.976 A:middle
element.

00:07:17.356 --> 00:07:18.376 A:middle
And there's no step two.

00:07:18.376 --> 00:07:19.096 A:middle
That's just it.

00:07:19.096 --> 00:07:20.906 A:middle
Mm-hmm. All right, so how do we

00:07:20.936 --> 00:07:21.336 A:middle
do this?

00:07:21.336 --> 00:07:23.206 A:middle
Well, we have four classes

00:07:23.376 --> 00:07:24.576 A:middle
across all the platforms.

00:07:25.226 --> 00:07:26.836 A:middle
For iOS and TVoS, we have

00:07:26.836 --> 00:07:27.686 A:middle
UICollectionView

00:07:27.686 --> 00:07:29.456 A:middle
DiffableDataSource and

00:07:29.456 --> 00:07:31.666 A:middle
UITableView DiffableDataSource.

00:07:31.666 --> 00:07:33.256 A:middle
And then on the Mac, we have

00:07:33.636 --> 00:07:34.306 A:middle
NSCollectionView

00:07:34.306 --> 00:07:35.276 A:middle
DiffableDataSource.

00:07:36.046 --> 00:07:37.696 A:middle
And common for all the platforms

00:07:37.756 --> 00:07:39.796 A:middle
is this Snapshot class, which is

