00:08:51.496 --> 00:08:52.926 A:middle
And as we walk through our

00:08:52.926 --> 00:08:54.496 A:middle
different examples today, we're

00:08:54.776 --> 00:08:56.216 A:middle
going to notice a repeating

00:08:56.216 --> 00:08:56.566 A:middle
pattern.

00:08:56.566 --> 00:08:57.956 A:middle
It's a simple three-step

00:08:57.956 --> 00:08:58.676 A:middle
process.

00:08:59.186 --> 00:09:00.986 A:middle
So anytime you want to put a new

00:08:59.186 --> 00:09:00.986 A:middle
So anytime you want to put a new

00:09:00.986 --> 00:09:02.186 A:middle
set of changes, a new set of

00:09:02.186 --> 00:09:04.296 A:middle
data into a Collection View or

00:09:04.296 --> 00:09:05.776 A:middle
UITableView with the full data

00:09:05.776 --> 00:09:07.976 A:middle
source, all you do is you create

00:09:07.976 --> 00:09:08.676 A:middle
a Snapshot.

00:09:09.306 --> 00:09:10.846 A:middle
You populate that Snapshot with

00:09:10.846 --> 00:09:12.296 A:middle
the description of the items you

00:09:12.296 --> 00:09:13.476 A:middle
want to display in that update

00:09:13.476 --> 00:09:13.856 A:middle
cycle.

00:09:13.906 --> 00:09:15.756 A:middle
And then you apply the Snapshot

00:09:16.116 --> 00:09:17.376 A:middle
to automatically commit the

00:09:17.376 --> 00:09:19.356 A:middle
changes to your UI.

00:09:19.356 --> 00:09:20.786 A:middle
DiffableDataSource takes care of

00:09:20.786 --> 00:09:22.386 A:middle
all the diffing and issuing the

00:09:22.386 --> 00:09:23.556 A:middle
changes to the UI element.

00:09:24.426 --> 00:09:25.466 A:middle
So let's look at a concrete

00:09:25.466 --> 00:09:25.946 A:middle
example.

00:09:25.946 --> 00:09:27.376 A:middle
I'm going to open up Mountain

00:09:27.376 --> 00:09:27.946 A:middle
Search.

00:09:29.046 --> 00:09:30.526 A:middle
And this is a fairly typical

00:09:30.526 --> 00:09:31.236 A:middle
search UI, right?

00:09:31.236 --> 00:09:33.086 A:middle
We can all look at it and reason

00:09:33.086 --> 00:09:33.966 A:middle
about what it does.

00:09:34.216 --> 00:09:35.826 A:middle
You might see this in a Contacts

00:09:35.826 --> 00:09:37.006 A:middle
app, for example, but in this

00:09:37.006 --> 00:09:38.736 A:middle
case, we're looking at mountain

00:09:38.736 --> 00:09:39.776 A:middle
peaks around the world.

00:09:40.626 --> 00:09:42.666 A:middle
So as you can imagine, there's a

00:09:42.666 --> 00:09:43.626 A:middle
search field at the top.

00:09:43.626 --> 00:09:45.046 A:middle
As I start typing in that search

00:09:45.046 --> 00:09:46.666 A:middle
field, we would expect to see

00:09:46.666 --> 00:09:48.556 A:middle
the list automatically filtered

00:09:48.556 --> 00:09:49.606 A:middle
to just the matches.

00:09:49.676 --> 00:09:51.426 A:middle
And we'll see that if I start

00:09:51.426 --> 00:09:54.176 A:middle
typing, we can do just that.

00:09:54.506 --> 00:09:55.456 A:middle
And it all happens very

00:09:55.456 --> 00:09:57.456 A:middle
automatically and with nice

00:09:57.546 --> 00:09:58.356 A:middle
animations.

00:09:59.656 --> 00:10:01.626 A:middle
This is all incredibly easy to

00:09:59.656 --> 00:10:01.626 A:middle
This is all incredibly easy to

00:10:01.626 --> 00:10:03.896 A:middle
do with extraordinarily little

00:10:03.976 --> 00:10:05.336 A:middle
code using DiffableDataSource.

00:10:05.336 --> 00:10:06.306 A:middle
So let's take a look at how it

00:10:06.306 --> 00:10:06.696 A:middle
works.

00:10:08.336 --> 00:10:09.976 A:middle
For this example, look at the

00:10:09.976 --> 00:10:11.456 A:middle
MountainsView ControllerSource

00:10:11.456 --> 00:10:11.746 A:middle
file.

00:10:13.486 --> 00:10:15.386 A:middle
And all the action starts when

00:10:15.386 --> 00:10:16.586 A:middle
the user types in the search

00:10:16.586 --> 00:10:17.136 A:middle
bar, right?

00:10:17.936 --> 00:10:19.256 A:middle
So we have our callback here,

00:10:19.256 --> 00:10:20.876 A:middle
searchBarTextDidChange.

00:10:20.876 --> 00:10:22.276 A:middle
It's going to be sent to our

00:10:22.276 --> 00:10:22.826 A:middle
controller.

00:10:24.316 --> 00:10:25.796 A:middle
And from there, we just call out

00:10:25.836 --> 00:10:27.556 A:middle
to our own performQuery function

00:10:27.736 --> 00:10:29.466 A:middle
passing it, the search text that

00:10:29.466 --> 00:10:30.926 A:middle
we got from that search bar.

00:10:31.306 --> 00:10:33.096 A:middle
Now performQuery itself is

00:10:33.096 --> 00:10:34.116 A:middle
remarkably simple.

00:10:34.676 --> 00:10:37.236 A:middle
All we do is call out to our

00:10:37.236 --> 00:10:38.106 A:middle
MountainsController.

00:10:38.106 --> 00:10:39.566 A:middle
That's our model layer object.

00:10:40.186 --> 00:10:42.106 A:middle
And we ask it for a filtered

00:10:42.106 --> 00:10:44.266 A:middle
sorted list of the mountains

00:10:44.266 --> 00:10:45.636 A:middle
that match our search term.

00:10:46.356 --> 00:10:47.566 A:middle
So now we've got that list of

00:10:47.566 --> 00:10:48.126 A:middle
mountains.

00:10:49.616 --> 00:10:51.046 A:middle
We go through that three-step

00:10:51.046 --> 00:10:52.156 A:middle
process that I mentioned.

00:10:52.196 --> 00:10:54.546 A:middle
We create a new NSDiffableData

00:10:54.546 --> 00:10:55.536 A:middle
SourceSnapshot.

00:10:56.476 --> 00:10:58.266 A:middle
Now this Snapshot is initially

00:10:58.266 --> 00:10:58.556 A:middle
empty.

00:10:58.556 --> 00:10:59.456 A:middle
It contains nothing.

00:10:59.456 --> 00:11:01.136 A:middle
So it's up to us to populate it

00:10:59.456 --> 00:11:01.136 A:middle
So it's up to us to populate it

00:11:01.136 --> 00:11:02.766 A:middle
with the sections and items that

00:11:02.766 --> 00:11:03.466 A:middle
we want.

00:11:04.296 --> 00:11:05.246 A:middle
In this case, we only have a

00:11:05.246 --> 00:11:06.646 A:middle
single section to display.

00:11:07.216 --> 00:11:08.436 A:middle
So we're just going to append

00:11:08.716 --> 00:11:09.896 A:middle
one section, and we're just

00:11:09.896 --> 00:11:11.376 A:middle
going to arbitrarily call it the

00:11:11.376 --> 00:11:11.976 A:middle
main section.

00:11:14.336 --> 00:11:17.356 A:middle
Next, we append the identifiers

00:11:17.356 --> 00:11:18.796 A:middle
of the items that we want to

00:11:18.796 --> 00:11:20.386 A:middle
display in this update.

00:11:21.156 --> 00:11:22.376 A:middle
Now formally speaking, we

00:11:22.376 --> 00:11:23.446 A:middle
usually pass an array of

00:11:23.446 --> 00:11:24.386 A:middle
identifiers here.

00:11:24.896 --> 00:11:27.126 A:middle
But in Swift, you can also make

00:11:27.126 --> 00:11:29.196 A:middle
things a lot more elegant by

00:11:29.366 --> 00:11:31.036 A:middle
working with your own native

00:11:31.036 --> 00:11:31.646 A:middle
types here.

00:11:31.646 --> 00:11:32.916 A:middle
So if you have a native type,

00:11:32.916 --> 00:11:34.456 A:middle
and it can even be a value type,

00:11:34.456 --> 00:11:36.486 A:middle
such as a struct or an enum, if

00:11:36.796 --> 00:11:38.396 A:middle
you make that type hashable,

00:11:38.506 --> 00:11:39.756 A:middle
then you can just pass your own

00:11:39.756 --> 00:11:41.076 A:middle
native objects in terms of the

00:11:41.076 --> 00:11:42.226 A:middle
Swift syntax of what you're

00:11:42.226 --> 00:11:42.716 A:middle
doing.

00:11:42.716 --> 00:11:43.796 A:middle
And we'll look at the

00:11:43.796 --> 00:11:45.106 A:middle
implications of how that works

00:11:45.106 --> 00:11:46.166 A:middle
in just a little bit.

00:11:46.526 --> 00:11:47.766 A:middle
So now, we've constructed our

00:11:47.766 --> 00:11:48.286 A:middle
Snapshot.

00:11:48.286 --> 00:11:49.036 A:middle
It's ready to go.

00:11:49.796 --> 00:11:51.876 A:middle
All we have to do is call to our

00:11:51.876 --> 00:11:53.126 A:middle
DiffableDataSource, ask it to

00:11:53.126 --> 00:11:54.766 A:middle
please apply that Snapshot,

00:11:55.196 --> 00:11:56.196 A:middle
animating the differences.

00:11:56.196 --> 00:11:57.776 A:middle
DiffableDataSource goes off and

00:11:57.776 --> 00:11:59.606 A:middle
automatically figures out what's

00:11:59.606 --> 00:12:00.906 A:middle
changed between the previous

00:11:59.606 --> 00:12:00.906 A:middle
changed between the previous

00:12:00.906 --> 00:12:01.866 A:middle
update and the next.

00:12:02.276 --> 00:12:03.496 A:middle
Notice that there's no code at

00:12:03.496 --> 00:12:05.296 A:middle
all here, where we had to stop

00:12:05.296 --> 00:12:07.186 A:middle
and figure out -- reason about

00:12:07.186 --> 00:12:08.286 A:middle
what we were displaying in the

00:12:08.286 --> 00:12:09.786 A:middle
previous update cycle before the

00:12:09.786 --> 00:12:10.306 A:middle
user type.

00:12:10.346 --> 00:12:12.206 A:middle
That one more character, it all

00:12:12.206 --> 00:12:13.176 A:middle
happens automatically.

00:12:13.176 --> 00:12:14.226 A:middle
There's nothing to worry about.

00:12:14.226 --> 00:12:14.926 A:middle
We're not dealing with

00:12:14.926 --> 00:12:16.976 A:middle
IndexPaths, which are fragile

00:12:16.976 --> 00:12:18.046 A:middle
and ephemeral, right?

00:12:18.086 --> 00:12:19.426 A:middle
They refer to a certain

00:12:19.616 --> 00:12:20.856 A:middle
particular update, and have a

00:12:20.856 --> 00:12:21.536 A:middle
different meaning and a

00:12:21.536 --> 00:12:22.306 A:middle
different update.

00:12:22.716 --> 00:12:24.166 A:middle
We're dealing with identifiers

00:12:24.166 --> 00:12:26.446 A:middle
that are robust and enduring.

00:12:26.566 --> 00:12:28.456 A:middle
So everything is just really

00:12:28.456 --> 00:12:29.236 A:middle
simple to do here.

00:12:30.636 --> 00:12:31.686 A:middle
Before we leave this bit of

00:12:31.686 --> 00:12:32.726 A:middle
code, I want you to notice

00:12:32.726 --> 00:12:34.376 A:middle
something about Snapshot, which

00:12:34.376 --> 00:12:35.326 A:middle
you may have already noticed.

00:12:35.326 --> 00:12:37.816 A:middle
It is a generic class in Swift,

00:12:37.816 --> 00:12:39.916 A:middle
so it's parameterized by the

00:12:39.916 --> 00:12:42.126 A:middle
SectionIdentifierType and the

00:12:42.126 --> 00:12:43.846 A:middle
ItemIdentifierType that we've

00:12:43.846 --> 00:12:44.696 A:middle
decided to use.

00:12:45.246 --> 00:12:46.536 A:middle
So let's look first at our

00:12:46.536 --> 00:12:48.226 A:middle
SectionIdentifierType, which is

00:12:48.226 --> 00:12:48.816 A:middle
pretty trivial.

00:12:48.816 --> 00:12:50.146 A:middle
This is a really handy technique

00:12:50.576 --> 00:12:51.906 A:middle
for the common case, where you

00:12:51.906 --> 00:12:52.906 A:middle
just have a single section,

00:12:52.906 --> 00:12:53.136 A:middle
right?

00:12:53.436 --> 00:12:54.936 A:middle
You can just declare an enum

00:12:54.936 --> 00:12:55.606 A:middle
type for this.

00:12:56.166 --> 00:12:57.436 A:middle
And one nice thing about enums

00:12:57.436 --> 00:12:58.376 A:middle
in Swift is that they're

00:12:58.446 --> 00:12:59.796 A:middle
automatically hashable.

00:12:59.796 --> 00:13:01.376 A:middle
Hashability is synthesized for

00:12:59.796 --> 00:13:01.376 A:middle
Hashability is synthesized for

00:13:01.376 --> 00:13:01.536 A:middle
them.

00:13:01.976 --> 00:13:03.246 A:middle
So here, we just have a trivial

00:13:03.246 --> 00:13:05.196 A:middle
case of an enum with one case,

00:13:05.196 --> 00:13:05.886 A:middle
and there's nothing more to do

00:13:05.886 --> 00:13:05.976 A:middle
there.

00:13:09.046 --> 00:13:10.076 A:middle
For our mountain type, we'll

00:13:10.076 --> 00:13:10.866 A:middle
look at our Mountains

00:13:10.866 --> 00:13:13.566 A:middle
Controller, which is again, our

00:13:13.566 --> 00:13:14.276 A:middle
model layer.

00:13:14.866 --> 00:13:16.586 A:middle
And here, we see that we've

00:13:16.586 --> 00:13:18.176 A:middle
declared mountain as a Swift

00:13:18.176 --> 00:13:18.746 A:middle
struct.

00:13:19.296 --> 00:13:21.066 A:middle
And we declared that struct type

00:13:21.066 --> 00:13:23.076 A:middle
as hashable so that we can use

00:13:23.076 --> 00:13:24.186 A:middle
it with DiffableDataSource

00:13:24.186 --> 00:13:25.586 A:middle
natively rather than explicitly

00:13:25.586 --> 00:13:26.966 A:middle
have to pass an identifier.

00:13:27.356 --> 00:13:28.816 A:middle
And the important requirement

00:13:28.816 --> 00:13:31.186 A:middle
there is just that each mountain

00:13:31.246 --> 00:13:32.906 A:middle
be uniquely identifiable by its

00:13:32.906 --> 00:13:33.516 A:middle
hash value.

00:13:34.086 --> 00:13:36.866 A:middle
So we achieve this by giving

00:13:36.866 --> 00:13:38.726 A:middle
each mountain an automatically

00:13:38.726 --> 00:13:40.786 A:middle
generated unique identifier.

00:13:43.016 --> 00:13:44.366 A:middle
And here, where we implement

00:13:44.366 --> 00:13:45.966 A:middle
that hashability conformance

00:13:45.966 --> 00:13:48.606 A:middle
that we promised, we use just

00:13:48.606 --> 00:13:50.916 A:middle
that identifier to provide the

00:13:50.916 --> 00:13:51.666 A:middle
hash value.

00:13:52.246 --> 00:13:53.156 A:middle
So in this way, we're going to

00:13:53.156 --> 00:13:54.496 A:middle
have each mountain, even though

00:13:54.636 --> 00:13:55.866 A:middle
mountains, again, are value

00:13:55.866 --> 00:13:56.206 A:middle
types.

00:13:56.206 --> 00:13:57.476 A:middle
They just get passed around by

00:13:57.476 --> 00:13:58.096 A:middle
copying.

00:13:58.356 --> 00:13:59.316 A:middle
There's no pointer you can

00:13:59.316 --> 00:13:59.746 A:middle
reference.

00:14:00.026 --> 00:14:01.766 A:middle
But the identifier and the hash

00:14:01.766 --> 00:14:02.886 A:middle
value specifically of that

00:14:02.886 --> 00:14:04.716 A:middle
identifier makes them unique

00:14:04.716 --> 00:14:06.056 A:middle
enough for DiffableDataSource to

00:14:06.056 --> 00:14:07.376 A:middle
track them from what -- one

00:14:07.376 --> 00:14:08.296 A:middle
update to the next.

00:14:08.506 --> 00:14:09.926 A:middle
And as part of hashability,

00:14:09.926 --> 00:14:11.486 A:middle
we're implementing equality

00:14:11.486 --> 00:14:12.466 A:middle
tests here, too.

00:14:12.946 --> 00:14:14.826 A:middle
So we've looked at how you issue

00:14:14.826 --> 00:14:16.216 A:middle
changes to DiffableDataSource.

00:14:16.216 --> 00:14:17.566 A:middle
What about how we set one up to

00:14:17.566 --> 00:14:18.056 A:middle
use?

00:14:19.146 --> 00:14:20.166 A:middle
Let's go back to our

00:14:20.166 --> 00:14:21.176 A:middle
MountainsViewController.

00:14:23.936 --> 00:14:25.636 A:middle
And conveniently enough, we've

00:14:25.636 --> 00:14:26.766 A:middle
created a function called

00:14:26.906 --> 00:14:28.066 A:middle
ConfigureDataSource, where we

00:14:28.066 --> 00:14:29.376 A:middle
configure our data source.

00:14:29.726 --> 00:14:30.806 A:middle
And it's really just a little

00:14:30.806 --> 00:14:31.516 A:middle
bit of code here.

00:14:33.106 --> 00:14:34.146 A:middle
So in this case, we're working

00:14:34.146 --> 00:14:35.666 A:middle
with a UICollectionView.

00:14:35.666 --> 00:14:36.666 A:middle
So we instantiate a

00:14:36.666 --> 00:14:37.876 A:middle
UICollectionView

00:14:37.876 --> 00:14:38.966 A:middle
DiffableDataSource.

00:14:39.446 --> 00:14:41.886 A:middle
We parameterize it with our

00:14:41.886 --> 00:14:43.696 A:middle
section and item types.

00:14:44.656 --> 00:14:45.866 A:middle
Pass it a pointer to the

00:14:45.866 --> 00:14:46.886 A:middle
CollectionView that we want to

00:14:46.886 --> 00:14:47.286 A:middle
work with.

00:14:47.956 --> 00:14:49.236 A:middle
Now DiffableDataSource will take

00:14:49.236 --> 00:14:50.546 A:middle
that pointer and automatically

00:14:50.546 --> 00:14:52.586 A:middle
wire itself up as the data

00:14:52.586 --> 00:14:53.746 A:middle
source of that CollectionView.

00:14:53.746 --> 00:14:54.766 A:middle
So there's nothing else for us

00:14:54.766 --> 00:14:54.906 A:middle
to do.

