00:22:28.666 --> 00:22:29.806 A:middle
In addition to being really

00:22:29.806 --> 00:22:31.466 A:middle
mesmerizing, and fun to watch,

00:22:31.726 --> 00:22:33.256 A:middle
this example is just a little

00:22:33.256 --> 00:22:34.776 A:middle
bit different than the others in

00:22:34.776 --> 00:22:36.706 A:middle
the way that we construct and

00:22:36.706 --> 00:22:38.346 A:middle
commit the updates.

00:22:39.036 --> 00:22:41.786 A:middle
So if we wanted to, if we were

00:22:41.786 --> 00:22:42.976 A:middle
just -- if our goal was just to

00:22:42.976 --> 00:22:44.396 A:middle
sort everything and jump to the

00:22:44.396 --> 00:22:45.616 A:middle
end state, we could do that

00:22:45.616 --> 00:22:46.116 A:middle
here, right?

00:22:46.386 --> 00:22:48.296 A:middle
This demo is set up so that we

