00:26:03.056 --> 00:26:04.346 A:middle
First, as we've seen all

00:26:04.346 --> 00:26:05.236 A:middle
throughout the demos, there's

00:26:05.236 --> 00:26:06.396 A:middle
basically just three steps.

00:26:06.666 --> 00:26:07.856 A:middle
You want to create a Snapshot,

00:26:08.906 --> 00:26:10.246 A:middle
configure it as you need it, and

00:26:10.246 --> 00:26:10.946 A:middle
apply it.

00:26:11.446 --> 00:26:13.096 A:middle
So you always want to call the

00:26:13.096 --> 00:26:13.806 A:middle
apply method.

00:26:14.256 --> 00:26:15.576 A:middle
Now conversely, you don't call

00:26:15.576 --> 00:26:16.766 A:middle
performBatchUpdates anymore.

00:26:16.986 --> 00:26:17.646 A:middle
That's old and dead.

00:26:17.946 --> 00:26:19.356 A:middle
Called insertItems, none of

00:26:19.676 --> 00:26:19.766 A:middle
that.

00:26:19.946 --> 00:26:21.266 A:middle
If you call these, the framework

00:26:21.266 --> 00:26:22.066 A:middle
will complain.

00:26:22.296 --> 00:26:23.846 A:middle
And, you know, you will see

00:26:23.846 --> 00:26:23.936 A:middle
that.

00:26:27.046 --> 00:26:28.306 A:middle
Okay, there are two ways to

00:26:28.306 --> 00:26:29.706 A:middle
create Snapshots.

00:26:29.766 --> 00:26:31.276 A:middle
And the most common way is to

00:26:31.276 --> 00:26:32.486 A:middle
create an empty Snapshot.

00:26:32.706 --> 00:26:33.816 A:middle
And here we see, we construct

00:26:33.816 --> 00:26:35.206 A:middle
the Snapshot with the types for

00:26:35.206 --> 00:26:36.996 A:middle
the sections and items.

00:26:38.376 --> 00:26:39.736 A:middle
And you can also create one,

00:26:39.736 --> 00:26:40.696 A:middle
like we saw in the last demo,

00:26:40.696 --> 00:26:41.896 A:middle
from the current state.

00:26:41.896 --> 00:26:42.766 A:middle
And this is very useful

00:26:42.766 --> 00:26:44.196 A:middle
sometimes when a certain action

00:26:44.196 --> 00:26:45.326 A:middle
occurs where you need to modify

00:26:45.326 --> 00:26:45.976 A:middle
just one little thing.

00:26:48.516 --> 00:26:50.036 A:middle
Now when you create this, you're

00:26:50.036 --> 00:26:50.936 A:middle
going to get a copy back.

00:26:51.056 --> 00:26:52.696 A:middle
So you can mutate that at will,

00:26:52.696 --> 00:26:54.066 A:middle
and it will not affect this --

00:26:54.206 --> 00:26:55.746 A:middle
the data source that it came

00:26:55.746 --> 00:26:55.976 A:middle
from.

00:26:58.186 --> 00:26:59.456 A:middle
Now once you have that Snapshot,

00:26:59.456 --> 00:27:00.836 A:middle
if you did ask some questions,

00:26:59.456 --> 00:27:00.836 A:middle
if you did ask some questions,

00:27:00.836 --> 00:27:01.686 A:middle
like, you know, "How many items

00:27:01.686 --> 00:27:01.856 A:middle
you got?

00:27:01.856 --> 00:27:02.746 A:middle
How many sections you got?

00:27:02.846 --> 00:27:03.946 A:middle
Identify the identifiers."

00:27:04.286 --> 00:27:04.846 A:middle
You can do that.

00:27:04.846 --> 00:27:06.296 A:middle
And there's a lot of API you can

00:27:06.296 --> 00:27:07.146 A:middle
check out in the SDK.

00:27:07.146 --> 00:27:07.976 A:middle
But here's a few of those.

00:27:11.156 --> 00:27:12.296 A:middle
All right, so I promise you no

00:27:12.296 --> 00:27:13.146 A:middle
more IndexPath.

00:27:13.146 --> 00:27:14.456 A:middle
So when we configured these

00:27:14.456 --> 00:27:16.496 A:middle
Snapshots, you'll never see an

00:27:16.496 --> 00:27:18.666 A:middle
IndexPath in this API, through

00:27:18.666 --> 00:27:20.516 A:middle
explicit API.

00:27:21.066 --> 00:27:22.506 A:middle
So, so far, we've seen a very

00:27:22.506 --> 00:27:23.846 A:middle
common pattern of appending

00:27:23.846 --> 00:27:25.226 A:middle
items and appending sections,

00:27:25.226 --> 00:27:26.026 A:middle
all those kinds of things.

00:27:26.026 --> 00:27:27.026 A:middle
But you can also do things like

00:27:27.026 --> 00:27:28.456 A:middle
insert and move and delete.

00:27:29.246 --> 00:27:31.226 A:middle
And all of these API's take in

00:27:31.456 --> 00:27:34.276 A:middle
other relative identifiers to

00:27:34.276 --> 00:27:35.596 A:middle
tell you where things go.

00:27:35.596 --> 00:27:37.426 A:middle
So if I want to insert 20 new

00:27:37.426 --> 00:27:38.746 A:middle
identifiers that are all unique,

00:27:39.686 --> 00:27:40.776 A:middle
before or after another

00:27:40.776 --> 00:27:42.736 A:middle
identifier, we have explicit API

00:27:42.736 --> 00:27:43.336 A:middle
for that.

00:27:43.336 --> 00:27:44.256 A:middle
So you'll say, "Insert these

00:27:44.256 --> 00:27:45.566 A:middle
identifiers before this

00:27:45.566 --> 00:27:46.236 A:middle
identifier."

00:27:47.056 --> 00:27:49.246 A:middle
Now, if you don't have anything

