00:28:35.046 --> 00:28:35.936 A:middle
Now in Swift, this needs to

00:28:35.936 --> 00:28:37.096 A:middle
conform to hashable.

00:28:37.526 --> 00:28:38.976 A:middle
And conveniently enough, many

00:28:38.976 --> 00:28:39.926 A:middle
things in Swift do this

00:28:39.926 --> 00:28:40.536 A:middle
automatically.

00:28:40.536 --> 00:28:42.356 A:middle
We saw auto synthesis for this

00:28:42.356 --> 00:28:42.976 A:middle
in the enum types.

00:28:45.646 --> 00:28:47.466 A:middle
And we have string, and integer,

00:28:47.466 --> 00:28:48.956 A:middle
and UUID, all these great things

00:28:48.956 --> 00:28:50.456 A:middle
that are available for use for

00:28:50.456 --> 00:28:51.286 A:middle
DiffableDataSource.

00:28:52.746 --> 00:28:54.636 A:middle
Now, we also saw that you can

00:28:54.636 --> 00:28:56.266 A:middle
bring in some model data into

00:28:56.266 --> 00:28:57.396 A:middle
these identifiers.

00:28:57.496 --> 00:28:58.626 A:middle
And this is really convenient.

00:28:58.996 --> 00:29:00.266 A:middle
Now your identity needs to come

00:28:58.996 --> 00:29:00.266 A:middle
Now your identity needs to come

00:29:00.266 --> 00:29:01.506 A:middle
from some unique identifier.

00:29:01.856 --> 00:29:02.976 A:middle
But you can also bring in other

00:29:03.126 --> 00:29:03.816 A:middle
attributes.

00:29:03.816 --> 00:29:05.536 A:middle
When we saw like the name and

00:29:05.536 --> 00:29:07.156 A:middle
the mountains, you can control

00:29:07.156 --> 00:29:07.666 A:middle
our example.

00:29:08.536 --> 00:29:09.426 A:middle
And this is really handy,

